txt.en: Drúadan corpses can be found in the wilds of Agarnaith.\n\nYou should burn Drúadan corpses and bring back their necklaces.

'On the way here, I found quite a few Drúedain bodies in the marsh. They must have fallen to Orcs or the treacherous wildlife. Do you see the necklaces they wear?'

He motions at the Drúedain standing before you. You notice they are wearing decorative necklaces of beads, bones, and feathers. Each is slightly different.

'Those necklaces may be distinct enough to identify their fallen comrades. Search the swamp, collect the necklaces, and burn the Drúedain remains before the deranged creatures of the swamp can devour them any further.'
Ghai-buri-Sêk can be found outside the mountain pass in Agarnaith.\n\nYou should talk to Ghai-buri-Sêk.
You give Ghai-buri-Sêk the necklaces you collected from his fallen warriors. You see several emotions flash across his face - sorrow, anger, and then gratitude.\n\n'Thank you.'
Many Drúedain have fallen to the wilds of Agarnaith since the mountain pass opened. You will likely earn their favour by showing respect to their dead.
